SUMMARY:Conservation Fair (South)
DESCRIPTION:Join New Jersey Audubon and local conservation organizations to learn about financial and technical assistance in your area! This event is intended for southern New Jersey landowners; a second event in northern New Jersey will be held on April 23rd. Following brief presentations\, we will provide printed maps of the specific location that you’re interested in restoring and you will be able to talk to industry professionals and receive tailored advice and schedule follow-up site visits for potential conservation work. \nTopics covered include habitat for grassland birds\, American Black Duck\, and Bog Turtle\, as well as broader conservation focuses like restoring wetlands\, forestlands\, and land preservation! Partner attendees include US Fish and Wildlife Service\, Natural Resources Conservation Service\, The Xerces Society\, and other local groups that can help you manage your land for conservation.  This will be held in the Millville Public Library ‘Gant Room’ \nPlease contact Kati DePaola with any questions at kati.depaola@njaudubon.org. \nRESERVE A SEAT
URL:https://njaudubon.org/event/conservation-fair-south/
LOCATION:Millville Public Library\, 210 Buck St\, Millville\, New Jersey\, 08332
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://njaudubon.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/CPF-eventbrite-photo-2.jpg
END:VEVENT
